      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of chart with Aug 8 article on New York City Police Comr Howard Safir's plan to resign</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, a chart yesterday with an article about Howard Safir's plan to resign as New York City police commissioner misstated the comparative numbers of killings in 1998 in New York and Chicago. New York had 628 killings that year, fewer than Chicago, a city less than half its size; the number was not 628 fewer than Chicago's.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Because of an editing error, a chart yesterday with an article about Howard Safir's plan to resign as New York City police commissioner misstated the comparative numbers of killings in 1998 in New York and Chicago. New York had 628 killings that year, fewer than Chicago, a city less than half its size; the number was not 628 fewer than Chicago's.</p>
      </block>
